cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY. 

The paper deals with a robotics problem of Vision-based Simultaneous Localization And Mapping (VSLAM) using a monocular camera. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper proposes an edge-based approach for VSLAM, which involves computer vision techniques such as edge detection and matching. Hence, cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also a likely category. The paper also discusses optimization techniques and non-linear optimization, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with a robotics problem, which involves control and decision-making, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible category as well.
